## **Featured Event Card Strip (Homepage) — Fill + Rounded Corners**

**Use when:** Featured Events horizontal strip (`FeaturedEventsSection`) — wide promo banners must **fill** the image column with **no left/right letterboxing** and **rounded top/left corners** matching the card (`rounded-2xl`).

**Reference implementation:** Align with **Upcoming Events** banner pattern (`UpcomingEventsSection` → `Link.block` → `event-card-banner-media--upcoming`).

### **Problem**
- Fixed `md:h-[200px]` on a **70%**-wide column + `object-contain` → very wide, short box (~4:1) → **side gaps** for landscape banners (e.g. Givebutter).
- Rounded radius on inner media only — contained image did not reach edges → **square yellow corners** visible inside rounded card.

### **Solution**

**1. Parent wrapper clips corners (not inner image box alone)**

```css
.featured-event-card-media {
  overflow: hidden;
  border-top-left-radius: 1rem;
  border-top-right-radius: 1rem;
  line-height: 0;
}
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .featured-event-card-media {
    border-top-left-radius: 1rem;
    border-top-right-radius: 0;
    border-bottom-left-radius: 1rem;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 0;
  }
}
```

Inner `.event-card-banner-media--featured-strip` uses `border-radius: 0` — parent clips.

**2. Mobile: compact aspect-ratio frame; Desktop: fill entire media column**

```css
/* Mobile — shorter strip (~25% less than 5/3) */
.event-card-banner-media--featured-strip {
  aspect-ratio: 20 / 9;
  width: 100%;
  max-height: 11.25rem;
  border-radius: 0;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .featured-event-card-media {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-self: stretch;
    min-height: 0;
  }
  .featured-event-card-media > a {
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    height: 100%;
    min-height: 0;
  }
  .event-card-banner-media--featured-strip {
    aspect-ratio: auto;
    max-height: none;
    min-height: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    width: 100%;
  }
}

.event-card-banner-media--featured-strip .event-card-banner-image,
.event-card-banner-media--featured-strip img {
  object-fit: cover !important;
  object-position: top center !important;
}
```

- **Mobile:** `aspect-ratio: 20/9` + `max-height` keeps cards compact.
- **Desktop:** Row uses `md:items-stretch`; media column + link + strip use **`height: 100%`** (no fixed `aspect-ratio` / `max-height` on desktop) so the image **spans the full left panel**.
- **`object-cover`** + **`top center`** fills edge-to-edge (no side letterboxing); crops bottom if needed — same intent as live event strip.
- Override global `object-fit: contain` with `!important` for featured strip only.
- **`EventStripBannerImage`**: `variant="featured"` must include `h-full w-full` on the media wrapper.

**3. Remove fixed row height** — no `md:h-[200px]` on card; mobile aspect-ratio drives height; desktop height follows details column stretch.

**4. Component structure**

```tsx
<div className="featured-event-card group overflow-hidden rounded-2xl ...">
  <div className="featured-event-card-inner flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-stretch">
    <div className="featured-event-card-media relative w-full shrink-0 md:w-[70%]">
      <Link href={`/events/${id}`} className="block h-full w-full min-h-0">
        <EventStripBannerImage src={...} variant="featured" />
      </Link>
      {/* absolute: featured pill, buy-ticket overlay */}
    </div>
    <div className="featured-event-card-details ...">...</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**5. `EventStripBannerImage`** — `variant="featured"` → `event-card-banner-media--featured-strip h-full w-full`; Next/Image `fill` + `event-card-banner-image`; `group-hover:scale-105` on featured.

