### **When to use contain vs cover**

| Context | Fit | Why |
|--------|-----|-----|
| Event thumbnails, sponsors, heroes (must show full art) | `object-contain` | Zero crop |
| Featured homepage **promo strip** (fill column, no side gaps) | `object-cover` in clipped parent | Full bleed + rounded corners |

### **Troubleshooting: Image cut off in middle / doesn't fill left column (desktop)**

**Symptom:** Featured banner shows only a horizontal band or empty space above/below; image does not span full height of the left media column.

**Root cause:** Desktop `.event-card-banner-media--featured-strip` used fixed `aspect-ratio` + `max-height` while `.featured-event-card-inner` uses `md:items-stretch` — details column sets row height but the banner box stayed a short fixed box.

**Fix checklist:**
- [ ] Desktop: `aspect-ratio: auto`, `max-height: none`, `height: 100%`, `min-height: 100%` on `--featured-strip`
- [ ] Desktop: `.featured-event-card-media` is `display: flex`, link is `height: 100%`, `min-height: 0`
- [ ] `EventStripBannerImage` featured variant includes `h-full w-full`
- [ ] Link: `block h-full w-full min-h-0`
- [ ] `object-fit: cover !important` + `object-position: top center !important`
- [ ] Parent `.featured-event-card-media` has `overflow: hidden` + border-radius (inner strip `border-radius: 0`)
- [ ] Do **not** re-add desktop `max-height` or fixed `aspect-ratio` on featured strip when row uses `items-stretch`

